{"id":27,"parent_id":6,"book_id":9402,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":27,"title":"Moses 7:21–41: Enoch Saw What Would Happen in His Own Day","subtitle":"","short_title":"Moses 7:21–41: Enoch Saw What Would Happen in His Own Day","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-721-41-enoch-saw-what-would-happen-in-his-own-day","content":[["div",{"id":"head22","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-721-41-enoch-saw-what-would-happen-in-his-own-day.head22"},["h1","Moses 7:21–41",["br"],"Enoch Saw What Would Happen in His Own Day"]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Some Important Principles, Doctrines, and Events"],["ul.bullet",["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Because of their righteousness, Enoch, the people of his city, and other righteous people after Enoch’s day were taken into heaven (“translated”) without suffering physical death (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.21,27"},"Moses 7:21, 27"],"; JST,",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/14.26-34"},"Genesis 14:26–34"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/5.24"},"Genesis 5:24"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/11.5"},"Hebrews 11:5"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/107.48-49"},"D&C 107:48–49"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.67-69"},"Moses 7:67–69"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Satan and his angels laugh and rejoice over the wickedness of God’s children (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.26"},"Moses 7:26"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/9.2"},"3 Nephi 9:2"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/5.19-21"},"Moses 5:19–21"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","God has emotions; He weeps in sorrow and His anger is kindled when His children do not obey Him (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.28-37"},"Moses 7:28–37"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/2.12"},"Judges 2:12"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/53.3"},"Isaiah 53:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/63.7-10"},"63:7–10"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/63.32-33"},"D&C 63:32–33"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","The “throne” of God (where He dwells) is a place of peace, justice, truth, and mercy (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.31"},"Moses 7:31"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","At death, the wicked go to a prison in the spirit world where they must wait in torment. After His death, Christ went to the spirit world to prepare the way for the wicked to repent and receive the gospel (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.37-40"},"Moses 7:37–40"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-pet/3.18-20"},"1 Peter 3:18–20"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/138.36-37"},"D&C 138:36–37"],")."]]]],[".topic",["h2","Suggestions for Teaching"],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.21-27"},"Moses 7:21–27"],". Translation"],["div",{"id":"p227","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-721-41-enoch-saw-what-would-happen-in-his-own-day.p227"},"Read aloud",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.21,27,69"},"Moses 7:21, 27, 69"],". Tell students that in verse 69 Enoch and his people were “translated.” This also happened to Melchizedek (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/jst/jst"},"JST"],",",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/14.26-34"},"Genesis 14:26–34"],"), Moses (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/34.6"},"Deuteronomy 34:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/45.18-19"},"Alma 45:18–19"],"), Elijah (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/2.11"},"2 Kings 2:11"],"), John the Beloved (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/7.1-3"},"D&C 7:1–3"],"), Alma (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/45.19"},"Alma 45:19"],"), and three of the Nephite disciples (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/28.6-8"},"3 Nephi 28:6–8"],"). Review the commentary for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.21"},"Moses 7:21"],"in the student manual (p. 22), and discuss with students the purposes of translation."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.26"},"Moses 7:26"],". Satan and His Angels"],["div",{"id":"p228","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-721-41-enoch-saw-what-would-happen-in-his-own-day.p228"},"Ask students to give reasons why people do what Satan wants them to do. Have them read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.26"},"Moses 7:26"],"and",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/9.2"},"3 Nephi 9:2"],"and discuss how Satan and his angels react when we sin. Compare this to the Lord’s reaction in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.28-33"},"Moses 7:28–33"],"."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.28-41"},"Moses 7:28–41"],". The God of Heaven Wept"],["div",{"id":"p229","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-721-41-enoch-saw-what-would-happen-in-his-own-day.p229"},"Invite students to think about the last time they cried. Then have students study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.28-31"},"Moses 7:28–31"],"and find reasons why Enoch was puzzled when he saw that God wept. Ask: What reasons did God give in verses 32–40 for the heavens weeping? According to verses 41, 44, how did Enoch feel after he understood the Lord’s answer? Ask students what these verses teach about the Lord."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.38-40"},"Moses 7:38–40"],". A Prison"],["div",{"id":"p230","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-721-41-enoch-saw-what-would-happen-in-his-own-day.p230"},"Ask students to compare what happened to the people in Enoch’s day who chose to follow God (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.27"},"Moses 7:27"],") to those who chose to follow Satan (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.34,38-39"},"Moses 7:34, 38–39"],"). Ask students what they think life in prison is like. Read and discuss the following scriptures that describe what life is like in the spirit world:",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/40.11-14"},"Alma 40:11–14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/138.11-23,50,57"},"Doctrine and Covenants 138:11–23, 50, 57"],"."]]]]],"refs":null}
